<span id="xv.iv.iv.ii-p1"></span> <span id="page_444">p. 444</span>
<span id="xv.iv.iv.ii-Page_444"></span><span class="c4"><span
id="xv.iv.iv.ii-p1.1"></span>Canon I.</span>

<span id="xv.iv.iv.ii-p2"></span>That the statutes of the Nicene Council
are to be scrupulously observed.

<span id="xv.iv.iv.ii-p3"></span><span class="sc"><span
id="xv.iv.iv.ii-p3.1"></span>Aurelius</span> the bishop said:  Such are
the statutes of the Nicene Council, which our fathers at that time
brought back with them:  and preserving this form, let these things
which follow, adopted and confirmed by us, be kept firm.

<span id="xv.iv.iv.ii-p4"></span><span class="c4"><span
id="xv.iv.iv.ii-p4.1"></span>Notes.</span>

<span id="xv.iv.iv.ii-p5"></span><span class="sc"><span
id="xv.iv.iv.ii-p5.1"></span>Ancient Epitome of Canon I.</span>

<span id="xv.iv.iv.ii-p6"></span>Let the copies of the decrees of the
Nicene Council which our fathers brought back with them from that synod,
be observed.

<span id="xv.iv.iv.ii-p7"></span><span class="sc"><span
id="xv.iv.iv.ii-p7.1"></span>Johnson.</span>

<span id="xv.iv.iv.ii-p8"></span>It is certain that Cæcilian, then
Bishop of Carthage, was present at the Council of Nice; that any other
African bishop was there does not appear; but probably he was attended
with several clergyman, who were afterwards ordained bishops.

